Block Chain Overview


### What is it?

It's a distributed ledger
Blockchain is "trustless"
Could be awesome for voting - banking - passport control etc.

## What makes it a distributed ledger?

Multiple individuals connect to the "core block chain network"
Each person has a full record of the leger
They will get updates when someone changes their copy
No central organization has the responsibility of updating and maintaining
Benefits: trustless - no middle men - no central point of failure


### What is a block?

It's a node in a linked list
it has data
it has a hash
it has the hash of its "parent node" (the one before it)

## What is the hash made of?

The data the block/node holds
AND - important - the hash of the node before it